      "span_text": "Independent variables utilized to adjust costs included age at episode date, gender, initial treatment (i.e. quinolone or macrolide), specialty of the diagnosing physician, the number of respiratoryrelated ambulatory care visits the year prior to the CAP episode, and baseline co-morbidities as defined by the Deyo adaption of the Charlson co-morbidity index (CCI). Because cost data were not normally distributed, costs were log-transformed."
